    "prompt": "<div>\n<div class=\"stimulus_reference\">\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure presents a diagram of a small sphere being thrown through the air. The sphere is initially located on a horizontal surface. There is a curved arrow extending from the sphere creating a parabolic path that ends on the horizontal surface to the right of the sphere. At the maximum point of the curve there is a point labeled P.&nbsp;\" height=\"103\" src=\"/images/4a85271917ccc642152d42518fbbfc8a.png\" width=\"400\"></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A small sphere is thrown through the air and follows the parabolic path shown in the figure. Point <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"P\"><math alttext=\"P\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>P</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> is the highest point the sphere reaches. Assuming air resistance is negligible, which of the following claims is true of the sphere while it is in motion?</p>\n",
